"title": "8279: innocence, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8279",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Innocence is displayed most purely in Jesus Christ but is also ascribed to others.</p>\n<h2>Examples of innocence</h2>\n<h3>Innocence before the fall</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:25\">GEN 2:25</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The innocence of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22\">1PE 2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:9\">ISA 53:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:19\">MAT 27:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:41\">LUK 23:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:46\">JHN 8:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:4-1John3:5\">1JN 3:4–3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Innocence in others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:21\">JOB 9:21</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:47\">JHN 1:47</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:9\">GEN 6:9</a> <em>Noah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:20-Judg21:22\">JDG 21:20–21:22</a> <em>the assembly of Israel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:6-2Sam11:13\">2SA 11:6–11:13</a> <em>Uriah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:15\">JOB 9:15</a> <em>Job</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:22\">DAN 6:22</a> <em>Daniel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:10-2Cor7:11\">2CO 7:10–7:11</a> <em>the Corinthians</em></p>\n<h2>The varied experiences of innocence</h2>\n<h3>Loss of innocence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1-Gen3:13\">GEN 3:1–3:13</a></p>\n<h3>The innocent wronged</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:22-Isa5:23\">ISA 5:22–5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:4-1Sam19:5\">1SA 19:4–19:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:1-2Sam13:14\">2SA 13:1–13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:20-Isa29:21\">ISA 29:20–29:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:16\">MAT 2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:1-Matt12:7\">MAT 12:1–12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:6\">JAS 5:6</a></p>\n<h3>Admissions of lack of innocence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:9\">2KI 10:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:1-Gen44:16\">GEN 44:1–44:16</a></p>\n<h3>Claims to innocence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:5-Job34:6\">JOB 34:5–34:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:1-Gen20:5\">GEN 20:1–20:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:26-2Sam3:28\">2SA 3:26–3:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:8-Isa50:9\">ISA 50:8–50:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:25-Acts20:27\">ACT 20:25–20:27</a></p>\n<h3>False claims to innocence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:34-Jer2:35\">JER 2:34–2:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:24\">MAT 27:24</a></p>\n<h3>Washing hands to signify innocence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:24\">MAT 27:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps26:6\">PSA 26:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:13\">PSA 73:13</a></p>\n<h3>A distorted view of innocence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:2\">PRO 16:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:7\">JOB 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:23\">JOB 9:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:28\">JOB 9:28</a></p>",
